# Code owners — Crystal Shell
#
# Once branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled (at
# publication, when the repo is public — same constraint as branch protection),
# any PR that touches these paths CANNOT merge without @aalonx's explicit review.
#
# We protect the GUARDIAN as much as the guarded:
#   - .claude/skills/  is read by agents as AUTHORITATIVE INSTRUCTIONS. A poisoned
#     skill is a prompt-injection / supply-chain attack on every user's agent.
#   - .github/         holds CI and THIS file — a malicious PR could otherwise edit
#     them to disable the protections themselves.
#   - install.sh / scripts/ run with elevated/session privileges at install/boot.
#
# Syntax: <path>  <owner>. Later matches win, so keep these specific.

# The agent skill — highest scrutiny, review every diff with a prompt-injection lens.
/.claude/skills/      @aalonx

# CI, PR template, and this CODEOWNERS file — the protection machinery itself.
/.github/             @aalonx

# Contribution rules and privileged executables.
/CONTRIBUTING.md      @aalonx
/install.sh           @aalonx
/scripts/             @aalonx

# Installed binaries — bin/ ships the session launchers and crystal-shell-mcp,
# the MCP server users' agent clients execute. A hostile edit here runs inside
# every user's agent session.
/bin/                 @aalonx
